A child was among three people killed on the N4 toll road this morning when a delivery vehicle overturned. The incident occurred between Mbombela and Alkmaar. Mpumalanga Department of Community Safet, Security and Liaison spokesperson, Moeti Mmusi, said that three people, including an infant, were declared dead at the scene. He said one passenger was seriously injured while another person escaped the accident with slight injuries. The cause of the crash is under the investigation.